BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bike to School Week
DTSTART:20260601T110000Z
DTEND:20260605T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260519T065516Z
UID:c576f8ab-3a84-52db-a8d0-273df3d4a213
DESCRIPTION:Register your school for Bike to School Week 2026!\n\nCommunit
 ies that embrace active school travel help their kids lead healthier lifes
 tyles and improve their school performance\, while also reducing traffic a
 nd pollution and making school zones safer for vulnerable road users. Also
 \, being able to bike to school with your friends is just plain fun.\n\nSc
 hools in Ontario are encouraged to register for Bike to School Week using 
 the form below and receive a suite of resources and materials to help orga
 nize bike-friendly events in a school environment.\n\n(https://www.bikemon
 th.ca/biketoschoolweek) REGISTER HERE\nURL: https://www.cycleto.ca/bike_to
 _school_week
LOCATION:
URL:https://www.cycleto.ca/bike_to_school_week
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bike to Work Day 2026
DTSTART:20260604T110000Z
DTEND:20260604T130000Z
DTSTAMP:20260519T065515Z
UID:f96f1148-9a39-52f2-ab2e-94f9f8915999
DESCRIPTION:Join us Thursday\, June 4th for the Bike to Work Day Group Com
 mute!\n\nBike to Work Day is organized in collaboration with the City of T
 oronto and has traditionally been the kick-off event for (https://www.bike
 month.ca/) Bike Month in June. Over a thousand commuters join Cycle Toront
 o and Bike Month partners on a morning group commute to Nathan Phillips Sq
 uare. We will ride together down to Nathan Phillips Square at City Hall fo
 r a community celebration with a Pancake Breakfast!\n\nWhether you ride ev
 ery day or haven’t ridden in years\, this event is for you. The official
  group ride will have well-trained Cycle Toronto Ride Guides to ensure rid
 ers arrive safely.\n\nWhen and where is the ride?\n\nThis year we will hav
 e four official start points across Toronto (see below). Three feeder ride
 s will coalesce at Bay and Charles\, enroute to Nathan Phillips Square for
  the post-ride celebration.\n\nWe ride rain or shine!\n\nMeet up Locations
 :\n\nCentral Meetup\n\n\n\nLocation - Bay Street & Charles Street - Southw
 est corner (south of Bloor Street)\n\n\n\nDeparture time: 7:30 AM\n\n\n\nR
 oute: Bay Street > NPS\n\n\n\nDistance: ~2 km\n\n\n\nTTC Access: Bay Stati
 on (elevator access)\n\n \n\nWestern Meetup\n\n \n\nLocation: Bloor Street
  & High Park Avenue - Southeast corner\n\n \n\nDeparture time: 7:00 AM\n\n
  \n\nRoute: Bloor Street > Bay Street > NPS\n\n \n\nDistance: ~9 km\n\n \n
 \nTTC Access: High Park Station (no elevator) or nearby Runnymede & Keele 
 Stations (elevator access)\n\n \n\nNorthern Meetup\n\n \n\nLocation: Davis
 ville Avenue & Yonge Street - Southwest corner\n\n \n\nDeparture time: 7:1
 5 AM\n\n \n\nRoute: Yonge Street > Charles Street > Bay Street > NPS\n\n \
 n\nDistance: ~5.5 km\n\n \n\nTTC Access: Davisville Station (elevator acce
 ss)\n\n \n\nEastern Meetup\n\n \n\nLocation: East Lynn Park (Danforth Aven
 ue west of Woodbine Avenue)\n\n \n\nDeparture time: 7:00 AM\n\n \n\nRoute:
  Danforth Avenue > Bloor Street > Bay Street > NPS\n\n \n\nDistance: ~9 km
 \n\n \n\nTTC Access: Woodbine Station (elevator access)\n\n \n\n*routes su
 bject to change\n\n Don’t own a bike? No problem! \n\nOur partners at (h
 ttps://bikesharetoronto.com/) Bike Share Toronto will be providing a LIMIT
 ED NUMBER OF COMPLIMENTARY bikes at the Central Meetup (Bay St. and Charle
 s St.). Bike Share will be onsite at Nathan Phillips Square to collect bik
 es at the end of the ride — so no need to find a station to dock your bi
 ke. \n\n \n\nSIGN UP IS REQUIRED - Please fill out this (https://docs.goog
 le.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdXWOLwa3_p6ESy2XJ2CqGjM2LK6PIqR8tMI-541ep3oE66Iw/
 viewform?usp=publish-editor) form if you are interested in borrowing a Bik
 e Share bike for the ride. Bikes available at the Central meetup\, Bay and
  Charles ONLY. \n\n Planning to arrive by TTC? \n\nPlease note that the TT
 C prohibits bicycles on the subway between 6:30 a.m. and 10:00 a.m.\n\n Wh
 at will the ride be like? \n\nOur Ride Guides try to keep a comfortable pa
 ce for all riders\; that means no matter your fitness\, age\, style of bik
 e\, you should be able to keep up a conversation. People are encouraged to
  have fun\, bring along music\, and wear what you’re comfortable in.\n\n
  \n\nWe will have one Ride Guide who will take the lead and navigate while
  another rides in the back to make sure all riders are safe and they can a
 ssist with any mechanical issues. \n\n Will the roads be closed for the ri
 de? \n\nNo. Since the last edition of this ride\, Cycle Toronto has taken 
 steps towards an Anti-Oppression and Anti-Racism Commitment that includes 
 finding alternatives to police escorted rides. We have opted not to invite
  uniformed police officers* to this year’s ride and will take advantage 
 of newly installed/improved cycling infrastructure where possible.\n\n \n\
 nAll riders will be expected to follow all traffic laws\, including signal
 s such as stop lights\, during the ride.\n\n \n\n*We have informed Toronto
  Police Service of our intent to hold the ride and cannot prevent them fro
 m arriving of their own accord\n\n Post-Ride Celebration Nathan Phillips S
 quare! \n\nAfter the group commute\, join us as we officially kick off Bik
 e Month with good company\, speeches\, exhibitors and free coffee and panc
 ake breakfast. We hope to see you there!\nURL: https://www.cycleto.ca/bike
 _to_work_day_2026
LOCATION:Nathan Phillips Square\n100 Queen St W\nToronto ON M5H 2N1\nCA
URL:https://www.cycleto.ca/bike_to_work_day_2026
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
